---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Quest Labs — The Science">

<!-- ── COVER ── -->
<div class="cover">
  <div class="cover-rule"></div>
  <div class="cover-eyebrow">Quest Labs · Scientific Foundation · Working Document · March 2026</div>
  <div class="cover-title">
    What Makes This
    <em>Different.</em>
  </div>
  <div class="cover-sub">The practitioner-researcher positionality, empirical foundation, and unique value proposition of the Quest Labs futures literacy ecosystem.

  <div class="cover-thesis">
    Quest Labs is the only futures literacy practice in the world led by a practitioner-researcher who trained <strong>directly</strong> with Miller (UNESCO), Inayatullah (MetafutureSchool), and Dunagan (IFTF) — with Stuart Candy speaking in her classroom — and who has <strong>20+ years of field-tested, empirically validated work</strong> to prove it. The ABCDEFG Futures Literacies Framework is not a proposal. It is a living, validated, doctoral-level contribution to the field.
  </div>

  <div class="cover-meta-row">
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <div class="cover-meta-label">Masters thesis</div>
      <div class="cover-meta-val">Freie Universität Berlin · 2026</div>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <div class="cover-meta-label">Empirical base</div>
      <div class="cover-meta-val">545 contributions · 170 educators<br>300 students · 30 teachers · Red Hook 2020</div>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <div class="cover-meta-label">IP</div>
      <div class="cover-meta-val">© Makēda — All rights reserved<br>Quest Labs holds license</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="page">

  <!-- ── 01 POSITIONALITY ── -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-num">01</div>
      <div class="section-title">Futures Research Influences</div>
    </div>
    <p class="lead">This is not a literature review. These are direct relationships — studied with, co-facilitated with, was taught by. The positionality is the methodology.</p>

    <div class="positionality-grid">
      <div class="pos-item pos-miller">
        <div class="pos-scholar" style="color:var(--teal)">Riel Miller</div>
        <div class="pos-year">UNESCO Futures Literacy Programme · Studied 2025 · Co-facilitated 2026</div>
        <div class="pos-what">Futures Literacy as capability, not prediction. Futures Literacy Laboratories. "Rigorous imagining." <strong>Makēda co-facilitated with Miller in 2026</strong> — direct practitioner lineage, not just academic citation.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="pos-item pos-inayat">
        <div class="pos-scholar" style="color:var(--gold)">Sohail Inayatullah</div>
        <div class="pos-year">MetafutureSchool / UNESCO Chair · Studied 2025</div>
        <div class="pos-what">Causal Layered Analysis. Futures Triangle. Narrative Foresight. <strong>Portal of Possibilities shared with Inayatullah directly.</strong> Now applying CLA through comic strips and madlibs — Makēda's original pedagogical innovation.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="pos-item pos-dunagan">
        <div class="pos-scholar" style="color:var(--violet)">Jake Dunagan</div>
        <div class="pos-year">IFTF — Experiential Futures Training · Studied 2025</div>
        <div class="pos-what">Experiential Futures Ladder. Serious games. "Better surprised by a simulation than blindsided by reality." <strong>Every interactive HTML tool in Quest Labs is experiential futures methodology</strong> in Dunagan's direct lineage.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="pos-item pos-candy">
        <div class="pos-scholar" style="color:var(--rose)">Stuart Candy</div>
        <div class="pos-year">Spoke at Makēda's class · Serious games + Library Project</div>
        <div class="pos-what">Co-creator of experiential futures (with Dunagan). His library project ties directly into <strong>digital positionality</strong> — a thread now embedded in the D (Dialectical) dimension of ABCDEFG, with viola, merch, and futures horizons already in motion.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="pos-item pos-milojevic" style="grid-column: span 2;">
        <div class="pos-scholar" style="color:var(--ember)">Ivana Milojević</div>
        <div class="pos-year">University of Edinburgh · MetafutureSchool · Narrative Foresight + Feminist Futures</div>
        <div class="pos-what">Narrative Foresight (with Inayatullah). Shero's Journey. Feminist eutopian methodology. <strong>The Shero's Journal — Makēda's applied work in Red Hook, Brooklyn — IS feminist narrative foresight made embodied, place-based, and Black and Brown community-centered.</strong> Milojević's scholarship names the gap; Makēda filled it in 2020 with 300 students and 30 teachers before she knew to cite it.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

  <!-- ── 02 ABCDEFG ── -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-num">02</div>
      <div class="section-title">ABCDEFG Futures Literacies Framework</div>
    </div>
    <p class="lead">© Makēda — All rights reserved. Masters thesis, Freie Universität Berlin, 2026. Doctoral work in progress, Humboldt University Berlin — where W.E.B. Du Bois studied. This is the contribution to the literature.</p>

    <div class="callout callout-gold">
      <div class="callout-label">The gap this fills</div>
      UNESCO's Futures Literacy framework is primarily cognitive-dominant. The ABCDEFG Framework extends FL into the full dimensions of human knowing: affective, behavioral, embodied, dialectical, creative, and generative: not tertiary, but as the primary perspective. This is what healing-centered educator professional development actually requires. 545 contributions. 170 educators. 2 gathering cycles.
    </div>

    <div class="abc-strip">
      <div class="abc-cell">
        <span class="abc-letter">A</span>
        <span class="abc-word">Affective</span>
        <span class="abc-desc">Emotion as data. Feeling as knowing.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="abc-cell">
        <span class="abc-letter">B</span>
        <span class="abc-word">Behavioral</span>
        <span class="abc-desc">Action in uncertainty. Embodied habits.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="abc-cell">
        <span class="abc-letter">C</span>
        <span class="abc-word">Cognitive</span>
        <span class="abc-desc">Sense-making. Mental models. Futures thinking.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="abc-cell">
        <span class="abc-letter">D</span>
        <span class="abc-word">Dialectical</span>
        <span class="abc-desc">Horizons. Digital positionality. Tension-holding.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="abc-cell">
        <span class="abc-letter">E</span>
        <span class="abc-word">Embodied / Experiential</span>
        <span class="abc-desc">Play as pedagogy. Being IN the future.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="abc-cell">
        <span class="abc-letter">F</span>
        <span class="abc-word">Fun / Creative</span>
        <span class="abc-desc">Joy as method. Art as futures practice.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="abc-cell">
        <span class="abc-letter">G</span>
        <span class="abc-word">Generative</span>
        <span class="abc-desc">New infrastructure. Not retrofitting.</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="abc-expanded">
      <div class="abc-row">
        <div class="abc-row-letter" style="color:var(--ember)">A</div>
        <div class="abc-row-body">
          <div class="abc-row-name">Affective</div>
          <div class="abc-row-text">Emotional intelligence as a futures competency. Feeling-as-data. Somatic knowing as legitimate epistemology. The body is an instrument and vessel, not a distraction.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="abc-row">
        <div class="abc-row-letter" style="color:var(--rose)">B</div>
        <div class="abc-row-body">
          <div class="abc-row-name">Behavioral</div>
          <div class="abc-row-text">How we actually act when facing uncertainty — not how we think we should act. Patterns. Habits. The gap between espoused theory and theory-in-use.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="abc-row">
        <div class="abc-row-letter" style="color:var(--teal)">C</div>
        <div class="abc-row-body">
          <div class="abc-row-name">Cognitive</div>
          <div class="abc-row-text">Traditional sense-making, mental models, systems thinking. This is where most FL frameworks stop. ABCDEFG starts here and goes further.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="abc-row">
        <div class="abc-row-letter" style="color:var(--gold)">D</div>
        <div class="abc-row-body">
          <div class="abc-row-name">Dialectical — yes baby 💅🏾</div>
          <div class="abc-row-text">Futures horizons. Holding opposites as generative. Digital positionality (Stuart Candy connection). Already alive in viola practice, merch, and music. Multiple truths simultaneously. This is the dimension that honors where you're from.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="abc-row">
        <div class="abc-row-letter" style="color:var(--teal)">E</div>
        <div class="abc-row-body">
          <div class="abc-row-name">Embodied / Experiential</div>
          <div class="abc-row-text">Jake Dunagan's experiential futures methodology made embodied. Play as pedagogy. Being IN the future, not just thinking about it. The game IS the learning. The sandbox IS the research.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="abc-row">
        <div class="abc-row-letter" style="color:var(--violet)">F</div>
        <div class="abc-row-body">
          <div class="abc-row-name">Fun / Creative</div>
          <div class="abc-row-text">Joy as legitimate futures methodology. Art, music, movement, play — not as engagement tactics but as epistemological modes. Blueprint. Baksana. The viola. This dimension argues that delight IS rigor.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="abc-row">
        <div class="abc-row-letter" style="color:var(--gold-pale)">G</div>
        <div class="abc-row-body">
          <div class="abc-row-name">Generative</div>
          <div class="abc-row-text">Building new infrastructure rather than retrofitting old systems. Quest Labs itself is G in action. The entire digital suite. The Open Collective. The crew. Building the new game rather than playing the old one better.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="abc-row" style="background:var(--midnight);">
        <div class="abc-row-letter" style="color:var(--gold-pale)">∞</div>
        <div class="abc-row-body">
          <div class="abc-row-name" style="color:var(--text)">CLA as Comic Strips + Madlibs</div>
          <div class="abc-row-text">Inayatullah's four layers taught through comic strips and madlib formats. This IS the pedagogical innovation — academic rigor made accessible to any human. Not dumbing down. Opening up.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mvp-box">
      <span class="mvp-label">Guiding principle</span>
      <span class="mvp-text">Minimum Viable Pedagogy — rigorous, accessible, and no more complex than it needs to be.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── 03 FIELD WORK ── -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-num">03</div>
      <div class="section-title">Empirical Foundation</div>
    </div>
    <p class="lead">This goes beyond the theoretical. This is crafted from and by real people in real places who engaged with this work and said something back.</p>

    <div class="field-cards">
      <div class="field-card">
        <div class="field-eyebrow">Futures Literacies Research · 2024–2025</div>
        <div class="field-title">Healing-Centered Futures Gatherings</div>
        <div class="field-stat">545</div>
        <div class="field-text">Contributions from 170 educators across two participatory research gatherings. The empirical core of the ABCDEFG validation study. Freie Universität Berlin Masters thesis data.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field-card">
        <div class="field-eyebrow">Shero's Journal · Red Hook, Brooklyn · 2020</div>
        <div class="field-title">Advisory Curriculum for Black + Brown Students</div>
        <div class="field-stat">300</div>
        <div class="field-text">Students engaged. 30 teachers trained. Feminist narrative foresight methodology (Milojević) applied in community context — before Makēda had the academic language for it.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field-card">
        <div class="field-eyebrow">International practice · 20+ years</div>
        <div class="field-title">Classrooms, Communities, Conferences</div>
        <div class="field-stat">20+</div>
        <div class="field-text">Years across Germany, Bronx, Alaska, international schools. After-school programs, SEL, restorative practices, cross-cultural education. The roots go deep before the framework was named.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field-card">
        <div class="field-eyebrow">Portal of Possibilities</div>
        <div class="field-title">Sandbox Sessions</div>
        <div class="field-stat">↗</div>
        <div class="field-text">Modified frameworks. Not workshops but sandboxes to play in… labs to tinker within. Rigorously delightful research environments ripe with new possibilities.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- ── 04 UVP ── -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-num">04</div>
      <div class="section-title">Unique Value Proposition</div>
    </div>
    <p class="lead">Why does Quest Labs exist and why now? What can niemand deny?</p>

    <ul class="uvp-list">
      <li class="uvp-item">
        <div class="uvp-num">1</div>
        <div class="uvp-body">
          <div class="uvp-head">Direct training with the field's originating scholars</div>
          <div class="uvp-text">Studied with Miller (UNESCO, 2025), co-facilitated with Miller (2026). Studied with Inayatullah (2025). Studied with Dunagan/IFTF (2025). Stuart Candy spoke in Makēda's class. This is not a reading list. These are relationships. The positionality IS the methodology.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="uvp-item">
        <div class="uvp-num">2</div>
        <div class="uvp-body">
          <div class="uvp-head">Empirically rich</div>
          <div class="uvp-text">545 contributions. 170 educators. 300 students. 30 teachers. 20 years. The ABCDEFG Framework is not a hypothesis. It is a finding.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="uvp-item">
        <div class="uvp-num">3</div>
        <div class="uvp-body">
          <div class="uvp-head">Fills a documented gap in the FL literature</div>
          <div class="uvp-text">Miller & UNESCO's FL is cognitive-dominant. Inayatullah's CLA was designed for policy analysts. Dunagan's experiential futures is design-focused. ABCDEFG is the first framework that centers the every day Mensch: affective, behavioral, cognitive, dialectical, embodied, creative, and generative. The field has been calling for exactly this. Makēda built it.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="uvp-item">
        <div class="uvp-num">4</div>
        <div class="uvp-body">
          <div class="uvp-head">Afroasian + healing-centered = unique epistemology</div>
          <div class="uvp-text">A fundamentally different starting point. Not "diversity add-ons." Raised in Alaska. Educated at Stanford. Practicing and learning to unlearn in Berlin. This cross-cultural, cross-racial, cross-continental positionality is a part of the method itself. </div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="uvp-item">
        <div class="uvp-num">5</div>
        <div class="uvp-body">
          <div class="uvp-head">The tools ARE the science</div>
          <div class="uvp-text">Every interactive HTML tool built for Quest Labs (Quest Cards, Black Menagerie, sandbox sessions, STEEPS Bingo, CLA MadLibs) is experiential futures methodology made operational. They are not illustrations of theory. They ARE the research instruments. Jake Dunagan's Experiential Futures Ladder in practice, at scale, with an educator community.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="uvp-item">
        <div class="uvp-num">6</div>
        <div class="uvp-body">
          <div class="uvp-head">The crew is already assembled across four countries</div>
          <div class="uvp-text">Germany, South Africa, Canada, USA. Seven people. Multiple disciplines. Ready to deploy. This is not a solo researcher with a good idea — it is a living collective with the infrastructure to scale.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="uvp-item">
        <div class="uvp-num">7</div>
        <div class="uvp-body">
          <div class="uvp-head">Play as pedagogy — joy as method — is scientifically defensible</div>
          <div class="uvp-text">The F dimension (Fun/Creative) in ABCDEFG is not soft. It cites Dunagan (games), Milojević (feminist eutopia), and two decades of practice showing that delight produces the psychological safety required for genuine futures thinking. Music, dance, viola, Blueprint, Baksana — these are research instruments.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- ── 06 RIIPEN ── -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-num">06</div>
      <div class="section-title">Riipen Students — Active Projects</div>
    </div>
    <p class="lead">Six universities. Six projects. All active. Students get real-world experience for credit. Quest Labs gets research, content, animation, and business infrastructure — at no cost.</p>

    <table class="riipen-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>#</th>
          <th>School</th>
          <th>Project</th>
          <th>Output for Quest Labs</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>1</strong></td>
          <td>CODCA</td>
          <td>Animated gameplay — STREAM Education</td>
          <td>Animated content for Black Menagerie + tools; STREAM framing for school systems</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>2</strong></td>
          <td>Montclair State University</td>
          <td>Business plan update</td>
          <td>International payment structure; Open Collective Europe; licensing model at scale</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>3</strong></td>
          <td>MacEwan University</td>
          <td>Research + methodology assistant</td>
          <td>Skim transcripts → macro-to-micro content; testimonials; warm data → LLM coding of ABCDEFG</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>4</strong></td>
          <td>Northeastern University</td>
          <td>Futures curriculum for college students</td>
          <td>YES — curriculum design using ABCDEFG + Black Menagerie for undergraduate futures literacy</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>5</strong></td>
          <td>Richard Bland College</td>
          <td>Sandbox session development</td>
          <td>Sandbox session structure + facilitation guides; documented for replication</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>6</strong></td>
          <td>Stanford</td>
          <td>Student athlete — research</td>
          <td>Research support; potential: embodiment + performance + futures literacy connections</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="callout callout-green">
      <div class="callout-label">Collective ask of all Riipen students</div>
      MacEwan student specifically: skim all session transcripts, organize macro-to-micro content, collect and code testimonials, and feed warm data into an LLM pipeline for coding the ABCDEFG Framework. This is the qualitative analysis infrastructure for the doctoral thesis.
    </div>
  </div>


</div><!-- end .page -->

